Content: I have ordered one of the game hacking 75T's with preloaded firmware (Pci-leech) , will see if it shows up on lspci off the bat.

Author: tishamdhar
Content: Hmm they are not super useful since Pi-5 GPIO drive for FPGA access is stunted we are better served with cheap dirtyJTAG's, they will be useful for stacking pi4's and more flexible layout, but without the PCI-e , do we really want pi-4's.

Author: carlfk
Content: no - but I don't think it helps, and might be worse than the current thing

Author: carlfk
Content: the FPGA board and camera need to be mounted somewhere - adding onto that pi holder seems harder than the little bundle of pi+camera+fpga board

Author: carlfk
Content: never mind harder - routing the usb and eathernet is impracticable - they would have to go over the top, and the dongle cables aren't long enough
